[
    {
        "content": "<p>As part of <a href=\"#narrow/stream/304641-ideas/topic/map2-based.20record.20builders\">rewriting record builders</a>, I'd like to make it possible to have bits that are included in the chain, but whose values are ignored. </p>\n<p>I think would be particularly helpful for parser combinators:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"kt\">Parser</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">combine</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">&lt;-</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">year</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Parser</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">int</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Parser</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">symbol</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">month</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Parser</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">int</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">_</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Parser</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">symbol</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"s\">\"/\"</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"nv\">day</span><span class=\"nf\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Parser</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">int</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"p\">}</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>However, it'd also be useful for <code>Task</code> when you only care about the result of some in the batch.</p>",
        "id": 446330173,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1719093060
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So the <code>_</code> would not record a value, but would still be able to lead to a failure that is recorded by the combined parser?</p>",
        "id": 446366581,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1719116557
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah, <code>Parser.symbol \"/\"</code> would still be chained with <code>Parser.combine</code> like the rest, but the value it produces would be ignored and won’t appear in the record</p>",
        "id": 446369955,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1719119073
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>So it produces the effect and failures can propagate, we just don’t care about the result ok value</p>",
        "id": 446370140,
        "sender_full_name": "Agus Zubiaga",
        "timestamp": 1719119265
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Sounds awesome</p>",
        "id": 446371032,
        "sender_full_name": "Brendan Hansknecht",
        "timestamp": 1719120137
    }
]